        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat(memory-core): make memory_search tool timeout configurable",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\n`memory_search`'s deadline was a hardcoded `MEMORY_SEARCH_TOOL_TIMEOUT_MS = 15_000` const — not config- or env-overridable. A single slow or cold cloud-embedding round-trip could trip the whole tool (and latch the 60s cooldown, surfacing a misleading \"embedding/provider error\") even though the local FTS/vec store answers in milliseconds. Operators running remote or under-provisioned embedders had no supported way to lift the cap.\n\nThis makes the timeout resolvable, with precedence:\n\n1. env `OPENCLAW_MEMORY_SEARCH_TIMEOUT_MS`\n2. `plugins.entries.memory-core.config.search.timeoutMs`\n3. built-in 15s default\n\nValues are clamped to `[1000, 120000]` ms; unparseable or out-of-range values are ignored at each layer, so a typo can neither disable the deadline (`0`) nor wedge a turn for minutes. The knob lives in the existing free-form memory-core plugin config — **no core config-schema/help/label surface is touched**, keeping blast radius to the one extension.\n\nAddresses **item 1** of esqandil/openclaw#4. Items 2 (split the query-embed timeout from the local-store search so a slow provider can't mask an instant local result) and 3 (stop reporting `index metadata is missing` on a provider timeout) remain as separate follow-ups.\n\n> **Stacked on #94564** (same file/area: the zero-hit forced-sync bound). The diff here is the two commits on top of that branch; once #94564 merges this collapses to the single timeout-config commit.\n\n## Evidence\n\n- New unit coverage in `extensions/memory-core/src/tools.test.ts` for `resolveMemorySearchToolTimeoutMs`: default (15s), valid config override, numeric-string config, out-of-range/unparseable rejection (→ default), env precedence over config, and out-of-range env falling back to config.\n- `extensions/memory-core` suite: **26 passed** (was 20 pre-change).\n- `pnpm tsgo:extensions:test` → exit 0, zero type errors.\n- `oxlint extensions/memory-core/src/tools.ts extensions/memory-core/src/tools.test.ts` → 0 warnings / 0 errors.\n- Scope: 2 files, `+122 / -2`.\n",
